Interface TabbableDialogElement

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CQInclude, Html5SmartImageWidget

    public interface TabbableDialogElement
    Used to indicate that a Dialog Element may be rendered either as a Tab or inside of a Tab

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods

      String getTitle() 
      Boolean isTab()
      Indicates whether an instance of the Tabbable element is to be rendered within a Tab or as a tab.

    • Method Detail

      • isTab

        Boolean isTab()
        Indicates whether an instance of the Tabbable element is to be rendered within a Tab or as a tab.
        Returns:
        True if the Dialog Element should be rendered as a Tab, false if the Dialog Element should be rendered inside an existing Tab.

      • getTitle

        String getTitle()
        Returns:
        The title of the tab to be rendered to an author dialog

      • setTitle

        void setTitle(String title)
        Parameters:
        title - The title of the tab to be rendered to an author dialog
